<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Penis contusion can occur
during sports games, when falling from a height on a hard object, or when
kicking in the groin area.&nbsp;Penis contusions can occur during cycling,
motorcycling, and horse racing.&nbsp;Frequent and strong blows from the
perineum against the seat (or saddle) can damage the genitals.&nbsp;Also, the
cause of bruises of the penis can be hockey and other sports, where it is
possible to collide with the enemy at high speed.&nbsp;This is especially true
when athletes neglect protective equipment.&nbsp;Penile trauma can occur as a
result of traffic accidents.&nbsp;Penile contusion occurs when the affected
organ was not erect at the time of injury.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:normal'><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Men involved in various sports (cycling, motorcycling, combat
sports, horse racing, etc.).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>How often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>You can get a bruised penis at
any age, but most often patients from 15 to 40 years old are admitted to
medical institutions.&nbsp;Various closed injuries of the penis, including
bruises, account for three quarters of cases of male genital trauma.&nbsp;In
children, a bruised penis is rare.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

